pageContext.description: Socket cylindrical (with slight ridge running up each side) + continued as a high, flattened midrib flat in centre and splayed or facetted at sides. Socket marked off from midrib by a hollow curved line; midrib decorated with a pattern of circles with dots in centre, lines of engraved ornament forming a triangular pattern down each side where blade joins midrib and similar pattern branching off up each side of blade, two incised bands with triangular bands encircling socket with zig-zag pattern between rivet holes across socket.
pageContext.collection: Museum, Leeds Phil. and Lit. Society.
